00:00:29.979 --> 00:00:36.040
portion of scripture, but also make some application for us with regard to our own church.

00:00:36.040 --> 00:00:39.700
And so Luke, excuse me, Luke chapter number five, we'll be looking at verses one through

00:00:39.700 --> 00:00:40.700
11.

00:00:40.700 --> 00:00:41.979
Let me read the account for you.

00:00:41.979 --> 00:00:48.180
In Luke five, beginning in verse number one, the Bible says this, and it came to pass that

00:00:48.180 --> 00:00:53.700
as the people pressed upon him to hear the word of God, he stood by the lake of Gennesaret.

00:00:53.700 --> 00:00:55.540
Now that's the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:00:55.540 --> 00:00:56.540
And think about that.

00:00:56.540 --> 00:00:59.979
They pressed upon him to hear the word of God.

00:00:59.979 --> 00:01:01.860
What a blessing it is to have a Bible.

00:01:01.860 --> 00:01:06.819
What a blessing it is to be able to hear the word of God preached and taught publicly.

00:01:06.819 --> 00:01:12.379
Of course, no greater teacher than God himself, the Lord Jesus Christ teaching.

00:01:12.379 --> 00:01:15.680
And what a blessing that must have been to be able to hear that message.

00:01:15.680 --> 00:01:17.580
And he's preaching the word.

00:01:17.580 --> 00:01:22.220
It says in verse number two, and saw two ships standing by the lake, but the fishermen were

00:01:22.220 --> 00:01:26.260
